man Emperor Otto the Great. She became regent after his death and was revered as a saint. The given name increased in popularity in England during the 19th century, when it was borne by the wife of King William IV; she was the daughter of the ruler of the German duchy of Saxe-Meiningen. The Australian city of Adelaide was named in her honour."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Adelaide de Vendôme was born in 1120, in Vendôme, Loir-et-Cher, France, her father, Barthélemy de Vendôme, was 30 and her mother, Guisburge Mondoubleau, was 29. She married Gosbert de Preuilly Seigneur de Bouchet about 1159, in Preuilly-sur-Claise, Indre-et-Loire, Centre, France. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. She died in 1195, at the age of 75."},"et":{"Cir 1120–Cir 1195":"1120–1195","1120–1195":"1120–1195","1120–1205":"1120–1205","1145–1211":"1145–1211","1167–Male":"1167–Surnud","1170–Female":"1170–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1090–1148":"1090–1148","1091–1142":"1091–1142","1091":"1091","1090":"1090","1142":"1142","1120":"1120","Abt 1159":"umbes 1159","1195":"1195","Cir 1120":"1120","1170":"1170","Cir 1195":"1195","1205":"1205","1148":"1148","1145":"1145","1167":"1167","1211":"1211","about 1167":"umbes 1167","Preuilly-Sur-Claise,Indre-Et-Loire,France":"Preuilly-sur-Claise, Indre-et-Loire, Centre, Prantsusmaa","Vendôme, Loir-et-Cher, Centre, França":"Vendôme, Loir-et-Cher, Centre, Prantsusmaa","Tours, France":"Archidiocèse de Tours, Prantsusmaa","England":"England","France":"Prantsusmaa","Vendôme, Loir-et-Cher, Centre, France":"Vendôme, Loir-et-Cher, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Cir 1120–Cir 1195":"1120–1195","1120–1195":"1120–1195","1120–1205":"1120–1205","1145–1211":"1145–1211","1167–Male":"1167–Kuollut","1170–Female":"1170–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1090–1148":"1090–1148","1091–1142":"1091–1142","1091":"1091","1090":"1090","1142":"1142","1120":"1120","Abt 1159":"noin 1159","1195":"1195","Cir 1120":"1120","1170":"1170","Cir 1195":"1195","1205":"1205","1148":"1148","1145"